column2: Less than two weeks till were back in this office. Bring on Hong Kong
Got a question about the #DSETENSEFE19? Put it below and well answer the best ones on our YouTube channel
Happy Birthday to our sporting and technical advisor Pedro De La Rosa

@andre_lotterer on a charge during the #MexicoCityEPrix. He started the race from P12 but made his way up the grid to finish P5..It was a crazy race, and we managed the energy well and came close to the leaders. - LOT
Garage Goals . Three of our beautiful #DSETENSEFE19s under the red lights of the @dstecheetah #FormulaE workshop, at the @dsperformance performance Versailles HQ
The one who falls and gets up is so much stronger than the one who never fell

All smiles after a great #MexicoCityEPrix weekend. It may have been a difficult race for us, but we ended on a high with a successful testing session. @jeanericvergne set the fastest time of the day and @andre_lotterer finished in the top 5. Now its time to analyse the data and get ready to come back stronger in Hong Kong

They boys have been busy with a successful morning of #FETesting. @jeanericvergne finished the session in 7th setting a 59.145 and @andre_lotterer was just behind in 9th with a 59.261. This afternoons session starts at 14:00 (GMT-6).

A tough race for us yesterday at the #MexicoCityEPrix, leaving us with mixed emotions. LOT battled hard and fought his way up to P5 after starting P12 on the grid. JEV wasnt so lucky, and after being hit multiple times during the race, he crossed the line in 13th. Now we re-group and set our sights on coming back stronger in Hong Kong .What did you think of the race? Put your 3 word race recaps below
Ready to get down to business With qualifying completed, we have our sights set firmly on this afternoons race. JEV will start 4th row of the grid in P8 and LOT will be in P12.
Cheetahs out on the morning prowl. Practice 1 is done, but theres plenty more action still to come today. #MexicoCityEPrix
Its Race Day! #MexicoCityEPrix
Gold + black + red = .@jeanericvergne heads out for Shakedown ahead of tomorrows #MexicoCityEPrix

Checking out the #MexicoCityEPrix circuit this morning! Its an impressive track. This year with Attack Mode being right at the heart of the stadium section, it really is going to be a spectacle for the fans! Looking forward to putting on a good show tomorrow

NEW VIDEO! What makes an awesome bromance? Who takes the longest to get ready? @jeanericvergne and @andre_lotterer answer your Instagram questions! Link to full video in our story today, or search DS Techeetah on YouTube.
We've arrived in Mexico ! Here are a few sneaky behind the scenes shots as the team setup the cars and garage for this Saturday's #MexicoCityEPrix. Where will you be watching from?

3 days to go. Heres your #MexicoCityEPrix track guide to get you prepped and ready for Saturdays @fiaformulae race..A little fact for you guys: The #MexicoCityEPrix circuit is the highest on the #FormulaE calendar. Well be racing at over 2500m above sea level

Who gets your #FanBoost vote today? Let us know below if youre giving it to @jeanericvergne or @andre_lotterer..Also, dont forget you can vote daily to give them extra power in the race. Link in bio. Thanks team
Smile... Its race week #MexicoCityEPrix
Buckle up.Were just ONE WEEK away from the #MexicoCityEPrix

Okay FE fam, question for you... Imagine mid race you pull into the pits to replace a damaged nose. Who are the 3 mates youd want on your pit crew to get you back out on track in quick time? Tag them below
That one friend who never reads the group chat about what to wear
Golden boys @jeanericvergne & Bajrami hard at work. Whats your favourite thing about the new #Gen2 @fiaformulae cars? Is it the speed, the design, the halo?? Let us know below
Counting down the days until we can go racing again . @jeanericvergne is patiently waiting to hit the #MexicoCityEPrix track... 13 days to go.

Black & Gold beauty Youve been asking for more close up shots of the #DSETENSEFE19, and were more than happy to deliver. Heres one of Keenes nose cone in hi-res from the #SantiagoEPrix..What details on the car do you want to see next? Put your close-up suggestions below for our super talented photographer @sam.bloxham to snap at the next race in Mexico

Cheetahs on the attack! Did you know that @andre_lotterers and @jeanericvergnes cars are named Keene and Bajrami after two cheetahs at the @thebigcatsanctuaryuk. Along with our adopted cheetah, Willow, were incredibly proud to have all three as part of the @dstecheetah family .

Congratulations to our man @jeanericvergne who has won the Grand Prix du Festival award at the 34th edition of @festival.automobile in Paris. The award is for his achievement in winning the Season 4 @fiaformulae Drivers Championship
Ripping up the road... Literally.The extreme heat of the #SantiagoEPrix left a few battle scars on the Parque OHiggins track.
Missed the #SantiagoEPrix this weekend? Check out some of our highlights from an action packed race in Chile. Next stop, Mexico!.The link to the full video is in our bio
Thank you Chile for putting on an amazing #SantiagoEPrix. We may not have got the result we wanted, but we had a great time racing here! Next stop, Mexico
Great to have @ritaora stop by the garage to wish @jeanericvergne & @andre_lotterer good luck for the race! #SantiagoEPrix
Time to shine under the Santiago sun - ITS RACE DAY!
A shot from Shakedown today, but can we replicate it tomorrow for another golden 1-2 at the #SantiagoEPrix
Track walk = . A completely new circuit for this years #SantiagoEPrix. It features the longest corner of the @fiaformulae season, stretching a massive 485m at turn 11!
Can we come out to play yet?.Just 1 day to go until the #SantiagoEPrix. Whats your 3-Word race prediction?
A great start to our #SantiagoEPrix journey! Thanks to everyone who came out to meet @jeanericvergne & @andre_lotterer at the @ds_official store in Chile .
250kW of power, 0-100km/h in 2.8 seconds and a max speed of 230km/h. The #DSETENSEFE19 both brawn & beauty
Youre absolutely glowing here @andre_lotterer .Want to give Andr a boost in the race? Click the link in our bio to give him your #FanBoost vote for today.
Fully focused and ready for the #SantiagoEPrix!.Click the link in our bio to give JEV your FanBoost vote for a boost of power in this Saturdays race.
#FanBoost is now OPEN! Lets get @andre_lotterer & @jeanericvergne back on the #SantiagoEPrix podium. Click the link in our bio to give them your daily FanBoost vote.
Oh #DSETENSEFE19 you beauty. Drop us a  if youre a fan of our Black & Gold stunner too!
Race hard. Laugh harder.
One day closer to being back out on track#SantiagoEPrix
The #SantiagoEPrix is just ONE WEEK away! @jeanericvergne & @andre_lotterer secured @fiaformulae's first 1-2 victory here last year. Will they do the same again? Put your race predictions below
Back of the pack, to 5th across the line! Checkout some of @jeanericvergnes race highlights through the lens of his onboard camera  #Repost @fiaformulae
Teamwork . Its #FeelGoodFriday, so we want to give a shoutout to our mechanics & engineers who work tirelessly on the cars to make them what they are today! #NotAllHerosWearCapes
Those curves . Throwing back to golden hour at the #MarrakeshEPrix where the #DSETENSEFE19 was looking mighty fine
The boys are back in town! Were off to Chile for the #SantiagoEPrix next week, home of our first ever 1-2 victory in @fiaformulae. Anyone fancy a repeat?
Sparks flying. Rubber burning.#MarrakeshEPrix
Golden opportunity - Keene heads out for a morning dash at the hands of @rossiterracing...@thebigcatsanctuaryuk

@jeanericvergne has had a few close shaves recently. What hairodynamic look do you think he should go for next? Does this Pogba style make the cut? .Were not even sorry for the awful hair puns in this post. If you have any that are just as bad, put them below. The pun with the most likes by next week will get a signed autograph card from JEV.

Qualifying in the back isnt the start you want but we had fun fighting our way through the grid to finish P6 in the end.  @andre_lotterer reflects on his successful #MarrakeshEPrix. He made up 14 places in the race after starting in P20 and crossing the finish in P6. Next stop, Santiago
ATTACK MODE activated. Time for this cheetah to pounce .Weve had two races now with @fiaformulaes new Attack Mode. Are you a fan of it so far? Let us know below
Good test for the team today, thank you @rossiterracing and @tatacalde7  Next up  the #SantiagoEprix - 26 January in
RACE HIGHLIGHTS Catch up on all the action as @jeanericvergne and @andre_lotterer went hunting in yesterdays @fiaformulae #MarrakeshEPrix. Watch the full video on our YouTube (link in bio).
What a race to the finish that was! JEV fought his way through the pack after an early spin, but secured 5th position. LOT found his way through the field making up 14 places from P20 to P6.
Ready to go racing ...#FormulaE #FIAFormulaE #morroco #electricracing #electricracecar #JeanEricVergne
Keene & Bahrain out on a morning prowl @thebigcatsanctuaryuk
Wakey wakey, Its race day  Whats your 3 Word Race Prediction for todays #MarrakeshEPrix? Put it below
Shakedown done Both cars looking good in the afternoon sun. Now we look ahead to tomorrow's #MarrakeshEPrix
Were excited to welcome @omologatowatches to the @dstecheetah family as a new partner to the team. #TeamOmologato

We have arrived in Morocco for the #MarrakeshEPrix! Just 2 days to go .Want to give us a Boost? Remember you can cast your #FanBoost vote for @andre_lotterer & @jeanericvergne every day! Just visit the link in our bio
Cheetahs always have each-others backs! Heres Martin and Keene from @thebigcatsanctuaryuk casting their #FanBoost vote earlier... but who will you pick? Click the link in our bio to vote once a day.

#FanBoost for the #MarrakeshEPrix is now OPEN! You have the power to give @jeanericvergne and @andre_lotterer a boost in Saturday's @fiaformulae race. Just click the link in our bio to vote..You can also vote on Twitter using #FanBoost + #JeanEricVergne OR #AndreLotterer. You can vote once per day too!!

Time to refresh our garage tunes ready for the #MarrakeshEPrix! Comment your song suggestions below.The best will be added to our Spotify playlist..Click the link in our bio to listen/follow our garage playlist on @spotify.
Just ONE week to go! Whats your 5 WORD RACE PREDICTION for the #MarrakeshePrix?

We're very excited to announce that @tatacalde7 & @rossiterracing will be back in the #DSETENSEFE19 as our drivers for the @fiaformulae official rookie test after the #MarrakeshEPrix!.Click the link in our bio to read the full story.
Ready to pounceWhats your 3 word caption for this pic of @andre_lotterer? Put it in the comments and well feature the best in our story tomorrow
The best is yet to come...Day 1 of 365

Theres always a few who get over enthusiastic with the champagne at the #NewYearsEve party .On a serious note, wed like to thank every single one of you for the support youve given us in 2018. We cant wait to come back even stronger in 2019. #HappyNewYear s!.What was you highlight of last season? Let us know below
From simulator to street circuit, what was it like for @tatacalde7 to drive the #DSETENSEFE19 around the #AdDiriyahEPrix track? Watch the full video to find out... just click the link in our bio.
#ThowbackThursday to our s on the hunt in Riyadh at the first race of the season. How many overtakes can you count on this clip?

Its beginning to look a lot like Christmas!  .Happy Holidays from all of us here @dstecheetah! Thank you for the incredible support youve given us over the last year... We really do have the best #FEFamily in the paddock. Enjoy the holiday break and well see you refreshed and ready for the #MarrakeshEPrix in the New Year .
Find a teammate who will sit by your car, make you laugh for 5 minutes, do up your helmet, and then send you off to set a lap. #Jeandre
We put @tatacalde7 behind the wheel of our #DSETENSEFE19 in Riyadh last week, but how did she find driving a @fiaformulae car? Click the link in our bio to find out in our new YouTube video.
Congratulations to our @fiaformulae Champion @jeanericvergne for being ranked the 3rd best driver in the world by @autosportdotcom
Leaving our (tyre)mark on the streets of Riyadh. The #AdDiriyahEPrix was the first race of the new Gen 2 cars. What do you think of our #DSETENSEFE19 in  mode?
The first race of the season may be over, but boy what a start it was! What were your favourite moments from the #addiriyaheprix?

A flash of gold What a drive by @andre_lotterer who started 7th on the grid and fought his way up to 2nd in the race, before a drive thru penalty meant he finished 5th in the first ever #addiriyaheprix..LOT: Its of course frustrating to have the issues that we had as I lost out on a potential win, or at least a one-two or a double-podium as we had the pace for it, but we gained some valuable points and thats what matters the most in this championship
@tatacalde7 getting to grips with the #DSETENSEFE19 in this mornings test session.

Starting where he left off last year! @jeanericvergne is back on the podium..After a thrilling race around the #addiriyaheprix circuit, JEV finished P2 and @andre_lotterer P5. Lots of positives to take away from this race to make us race ready for Marrakesh next month.
250kW never looked so good. After a qualifying session full of thrills, spills, and a few Red Flags thrown in for good measure, we have provisionally qualified in 7th (JEV) & 10th (LOT).
No on track action so far this morning. Both FP1 & FP2 have been cancelled due to rain  Guess well have to wait a little longer to release this Cheetah into the wild
NEWS: Were very excited to announce that weve signed a long term contract with the reigning @fiaformulae champion @jeanericvergne.

ONE DAY TO GO!! Its race day tomorrow, but dont forget you can still give these two s a boost. Head to the #FanBoost story on our IG profile, then swipe up to vote for #JeanEricVergne & #AndreLotterer..Watch out for our stories later today as the new #DSETENSEFE19 hits the #addiriyaheprix circuit for the first time in Shakedown @ 14:30 GMT+3.

When Cheetah met Falcon. We have arrived in Saudi Arabia ahead of this Saturdays #addiriyaheprix and @jeanericvergne has been making friends with the locals..Swipe across to see more of what weve been up to today.

This year, there are two ways to receive a boost of power during the race! .1) #FanBoost which allows you to vote for your favourite @fiaformulae drivers (*cough* #JeanEricVergne & #AndreLotterer *cough*). To vote, just go to our IG profile and click the FanBoost story highlight. Then swipe up to go to the FanBoost website and vote! Oh and 5 drivers get FanBoost this year .2) ATTACK MODE! Attack mode allows the drivers to get an additional power boost. However to gain it, you must drive off the racing line and pass through an activation zone..Which one are you excited to see @jeanericvergne & @andre_lotterer use in season 5?

Its officially race week, which means #FanBoost is now OPEN! You can give @andre_lotterer & @jeanericvergne a physical boost in this weekends #addiriyaheprix. HOW?...Just click the Fanboost story highlight on our Insta profile, then swipe up to vote for your 2 favourite @dstecheetah drivers..Once youve voted, let us know by putting  in the comments so we can say thanks!

The countdown is on! Just 6 days remain until the start of the @fiaformulae season  .Catch @jeanericvergne & @andre_lotterer on #Italia1s TV special Road to Formula E today @ 14:00 (GMT +1).@sportmediaset @ronny.mengo.

#Jeandre are back on track next week!! But how did our driver bromance begin? @andre_lotterer reveals all in @fiaformulae's latest episode of Off The Grid..Watch the full video on Formula E's YouTube Channel
Waiting for the @fiaformulae season to start like...

It's #InternationalCheetahDay! The perfect excuse to share this incredibly cute pic of Willow, our newly adopted Cheetah from @thebigcatsanctuaryuk..Cheetah's are the worlds fastest land animal and can reach 112km/h in just three seconds... Almost as fast as our #DSETENSEFE19. .Find out more at: thebigcatsanctuary.org
At the @autosportdotcom awards tonight celebrating one incredible @fiaformulae season and a new partnership between the Motorsport Network and SECA

How do rock climbing, photography and classic cars help prepare you for season 5 of @fiaformulae? Go behind the scenes with @andre_lotterer in #OffTheGrid to find out..Full episode out now on the Formula E YouTube channel.

Electric street racing in the heart of the Balkans anyone? @jeanericvergne and our team president @edmundyechu have been with The Mayor of #Sarajevo @abdulah_skaka and @sarajevo_sports this morning, supporting the bid to host a @fiaformulae race here in Season 6.
Action of the year. Say no more  Just click the link in our bio to vote for the #Jeandre action from the @fiaformulae #SantiagoEprix for the @FIA Action of the Year  @jeanericvergne @Andre_Lotterer

Happy Birthday to our very own @andre_lotterer! We want to give Andr a card full of birthday messages, so write yours in the comments below. We'll give him the card on our IG story at the first race

Remember remember, the 5th of November ... Is 40 days till the start of @fiaformulae in Saudi Arabia..Wishing all of our #DSTECHEETAH family a safe and 'banging' Bonfire Night

We're incredibly proud to be the only team to have two drivers nominated at this years @autosportdotcom awards. @jeanericvergne is up for Racing Driver of the Year and @andre_lotterer is nominated for Rookie of the Year. Want to support the boys? Head over to the link in our bio to give them your votes.

When speed meets beauty. #DSETENSEFE19

Andr: We did a good job at understanding the car even more. We have a lot of data to finalise to make sure we improve another step for Ad Diriyah. All in all, I'm really happy with how the car behaves and all the systems. - @andre_lotterer gives his thoughts on #FETesting in #Valencia. Swipe across to see what else Andr had to say..What would your testing quote be? Put your thoughts in the comments so we can read them
250 kW of power, 0-100km/h in 2.8s and a max speed of 230km/h. The #DSETENSEFE19... Blink and youll miss it

JEV: Testing has gone very well. So far Ive been very happy with what Ive seen. I also see a lot of improvements in many areas and the car behaves well. Theres still a lot to come with understanding the car and systems. We now need to go back and analyse everything ready for Ad Diriyah. - @jeanericvergne's got plenty to smile about after a successful pre-season test in #Valencia.

Need help getting over the Monday blues? Just swipe left to see some of our #DSTECHEETAH stats from last weeks pre-season testing @circuitvalencia..We completed 397 laps for #FETesting last week and after three great days on track, our drivers finished 2nd & 5th overall.

Setting fire to the rain . The boys have been lighting up the timing screens during this mornings #FETesting session @circuitvalencia. @jeanericvergne finished P2 with a 1:25.258 and @andre_lotterer in P10 with a 1:26.571..Well be back on track for the final session at 14:00 (CEST).
No on-track action today as its been a busy day of interviews and media shoots for the team. Dont worry though, were back in the car for the final day of #FETesting tomorrow from 9:00 (CEST).
I think weve found an 8th wonder of the world, and its a view everyone should see! Tag someone you would take to a @fiaformulae race to experience this beautiful sight
The car felt great! - @andre_lotterer after a successful first testing session yesterday. Were looking forward to hitting the track again today to continue perfecting the #DSETENSEFE19.

A great first testing session comes to a close in Valencia. @jeanericvergne finished P4 with a 1:18.033 and @andre_lotterer finished P5 with 1:18.227. Cant wait to get back on track for session 2 at 14:00 (CEST).

#ABBFormulaE testing is GO! @jeanericvergne takes the #DSETENSEFE19 for an early morning run here in #Valencia..Keep an eye on our IG story for more behind-the-scenes action from all three testing days this week.

Three days of @fiaformulae pre-season testing kicks off tomorrow in #Valencia.... and we can't wait! Swipe across to see the track map and circuit stats for testing..We'll be keeping you up to date with all of the behind-the-scenes and on-track action right here on Instagram!
Pre-season testing starts on Tuesday. We've got some big decisions to make before then... Like what music makes it onto our garage playlist??? Suggestions please
The @dstecheetah boys are out in force this weekend for @fiawec_official's 6 hours of Fuji! Good luck to @andre_lotterer & his race engineer Fabrice, @jeanericvergne and @rossiterracing.

To our friends at Renault. We would like to say a big thank you for the last two years and especially for this season. It's been a very special one! Thanks for your time in @fiaformulae and we're wishing you every success in the future. Merci et au Revoir.

What a team. What a season! 4 wins, 8 podiums, 4 pole positions, 11 superpole shootouts and a newly-crowned @fiaformulae champion. Thank you from all of us at TECHEETAH for your support this season. #ABBFormulaE // @FIAFormulaE // #PowerFocusBalance

About last night - what a way to mark the end of the season, celebrate the newly-crowned champion @jeanericvergne and realise just how much our team achieved this year.#ABBFormulaE // @FIAFormulaE // #PowerFocusBalance // #TheUnderCats
Your Modis Engineer of the Year - our Racing Director Lo Thomas!

Mark Preston: What can I say. This has been a wonderful season. Against all the odds, we have built a team that is capable of taking on the best manufacturers in the championship and compete right to the very end. To miss out on the Team Championship will hurt for a little while, but takes nothing away from what we achieved and from winning the Drivers Championship. To do the double would have been the icing on the cake but nevertheless this gives us more fire in our belly in our preparation for next season.

@andre_lotterer: It has been an incredible season for us. The whole team must be extremely proud of everything we achieved. The amount of work that goes into the team behind the scenes and the level of preparation is amazing. While today could have gone better, I accept the decision of the stewards and it is a shame to miss out on winning the Team Championship by such a small margin. Even so, this makes us hungrier for more. Its been a fascinating rookie season for me in this championship and I have learned a lot. We are all so excited to go racing with the Gen2 car next season.#ABBFormulaE #PowerFocusBalance @fiaformulae

@jeanericvergne: It feels great to sign off the season in style with another race win. Id like to thank the whole team for all the hard work this season and for the results we have earned, against the odds. This season has been the highlight of my career. We are a small customer team and honestly, we have done something amazing this year, going up against other manufacturers and coming within two points of a double championship win. This weekend couldnt have been any better, despite starting with a disqualification in qualifying yesterday, I came through to win the Drivers Championship. And again, today we qualified well in the wet, made a strong start and I could manage the race. It was tough because we know how strong the Audis are in the race. No mistakes were allowed on my side and I achieved that. I feel even hungrier now to win more races and thats the attitude Im going to have for next season. Im looking forward to it already. #ABBFormulaE #PowerFocusBalance @fiaformulae

@andre_lotterer: I am gutted that I was just off the podium in Zurich. I was feeling very good in the car and ended up fighting in some very tense battles for the win! The pit stops came and we were sitting very nicely near the front until the penalties. I guess it just wasnt our day, but I felt on top form in my cockpit, setting the fastest lap late on. P4 means more points for the team and every point is crucial at this stage with only two races left after this race. #TECHEETAH #FormulaE #Racing #Motorsport #ZurichEprix #ABBFormulaE #LOT18

@jeanericvergne: "Qualifying in Zurich was a mystery, I felt like I had the best car I've ever had in @fiaformulae so far, and yet we were the slowest, so we will look into this and fix whatever the issue was.The team really gave me a good car for the race, I had an incredible race pace and managed to overtake some drivers two, three times. It's a real shame about the penalty and our mistake in the car change where the car didn't slot into gear and I lost six, seven seconds. I could have finished second if we hadn't had these issues which would have been ideal, but now we take the title fight to New York. We will learn from our mistakes this weekend and we will come back much stronger. We're feeling positive about the final race weekend of Season Four and I'm hungry for success in New York." #TECHEETAH #FormulaE #racing #motorsport #ZurichEprix #ABBFormulaE #JEV25

Rome was a challenging but its great to come away with our sixth top five finish of the season and more points for the championship. I was simply too slow in Rome and we need to understand why. I dont feel any added pressure going into Paris, we continue to focus on scoring points and thats what its all about. Theres no point in stressing about the championship or adding that additional pressure as no good comes from it. So instead, we focus on what we can improve and how we can score as many points as possible for the coming races, said @jeanericvergne on the @fiaformulae #RomeEprix

First of all, Id like to thank my team who are always there to support me and help us push forward. Im still learning and they are an invaluable help as the competition in Formula E is fierce. Everyone here knows exactly what they are doing and I need to be at the same level to be able to win. Im happy with my second podium position this season but I want that win and thats what were aiming for.My first stint was ok and I was battling with Mitch. I was hoping to get out ahead of the pitstop but we were a bit slow and had to pick up the chase on the track instead. I saved too much energy in the middle of the second stint so Lucas overtook me and I thought that I maybe could take him back at one point but couldnt in the end. Its a great track here and a fantastic venue. The podium is probably the nicest podium Ive been on after Le Mans and its great to be back up there for the second time in my rookie season, said @andre_lotterer on the @fiaformulae #RomeEPrix

Championship leader @jeanericvergne on the #MexicoCityEprix  Mexico last year was my second podium with TECHEETAH and it was a crazy race. I love racing in Mexico not just because of the track layout but because of the amazing fans. Theres nothing better than hearing the fans cheering you on when youre on the starting grid, you can really feel the electricity of emotions in the air, its unbeatable. I dont feel any additional pressure going into this round as championship leader. For me, its always one race at the time, no matter where in the standings I am. Its still a long way to go in the championship, all drivers and teams in this championship are highly skilled and the competition is fierce. The whole team has been working really hard to come as prepared as possible so that we can continue to fight at the front. ABBFormulaE #Motorsport #TEHCEETAH #PowerFocusBalance

@Andre_Lotterer on Round Five of the @fiaformulae championship   The Mexico City E-Prix will be a new track and a new challenge for me. Quite a lot of the other drivers have got previous Formula E experience on this track but I dont see that as problem, I see it as a fun challenge. Jean-ric and the team have raced here before which helps a lot in terms of prep. Im really looking forward to driving the track, it looks like its going to be a lot of fun." Having my first Formula E podium only four races into my rookie season was great but I think the overall performance of the Santiago E-Prix is what Im really pleased with. We knew it was going to take some time for me to get used to the car and the set-up of the series, and I feel like it all came together in Chile. I had good pace in both the practice sessions and topped the qualifying session before super pole. Even though theres still some fine-tuning to do, I feel a lot more confident in the car now and I feel ready to start chasing the front pack together with Jean-ric. #ABBFormulaE #Motorsport #TEHCEETAH #PowerFocusBalance

@andre_lotterer on his incredible #SantiagoEprix Last weekend was great! It was really good to have secured my first @fiaformulae podium and to be up there together with @jeanericvergne as the race winner was a special moment for both me and the team. Im really pleased with a second today. Its still a long season to go and well continue to work hard and take things race by race. Racing on the streets of Santiago has been amazing, having full grandstands and the fans cheering their hearts out as we entered the grid was really special. #ABBFormulaE #Motorsport #PowerFocusBalance

Its fantastic to secure my second @fiaformulae win and my sixth pole position. I qualified on pole and I won the race, it cant get any better than that. I would like to thank the whole team for all the hard work and effort that theyve put in. Its really nice to see that a customer team can be up there fighting with the manufacturers in such a competitive series as Formula E. "The championship is all about collecting points and the win and second positions today has definitely continued to push us in the right direction. Id also like to congratulate Andr on his first podium finish, well both continue to push hard for the rest of the season. Ive loved every moment of this race, the fans here are just incredible and I hope that we get to come back here next year and do it all again, said @jeanericvergne on the #SantiagoEprix#ABBformulaE #Motorsport #PowerFocusBalance #TECHEETAH #JEV25

Cheetahs are one of the ten spieces particularly threatened by climate change and we're incredibly proud to have been part of the initial phase to raise awareness for the plight of them in the viral video where the @fiaformulae car with @jeanericvergne at the wheel, raced against a cheetah in a drag race over 100m. You can watch the full behind the scenes documentary here: http://bit.ly/CheetahVsFEcarWe have been absolutely overwhelmed by the support we've seen across the globe from news outlets and all of you amazing fans alike, so all we can say is thank you and stay tuned for the next phase in this project. You will not be disappointed.Together we can make a difference! #Wildlife #Cheetah #FormulaE #FocusPowerBalance

"Marrakesh was a really good race, I finished 5th which is a great position to end up as I started in P13. I did the best I could with the car, we still have some more pace to find to make gains in performance to be running in the front. We have one of the best powertrains in the paddock but were still working on our performance set up, said @JeanEricVergne on the third round of the @fiaformulae championship.

We were really close to a double-points finish in the #MarrakeshEprix before a hardware malfunction caused us to retire my car. It's unfortunate that it happened when we were so close to our first double-points finish for the season, but it's something that we hope to rectify at the #SantiagoEprix!" @andre_lotterer on his third start in the @fiaformulae championship and looking ahead to the fourth round. #FormulaE #Racing #Motorsport #Competing #Championship #TecheetahFE #PowerFocusBalance #SantiagoEprix

@andre_lotterer joins TECHEETAH to make @fiaformulae debut. He is set to partnerSeason 3 race winner @jeanericvergne as both drivers ready themselves to contest the forthcoming FIA Formula E seasons. Full story through the link in bio.Ivan Yim, Managing Director, TECHEETAH Formula-E Team:Jean-Eric Vergne and Andre Lotterer will form one of the strongest driver line ups in Formula E. I'm sure our two drivers will push each other to new levels of performance. Andres track record and experience with some of motorsports most significant factory teams, bringsimmense value as we push our own development in both the medium and long term.Andre Lotterer:I am honoured and proud to join TECHEETAH to make my Formula-E debut. Formula E has been the most exciting motor racing series in recent years. TECHEETAH made averybig impression last season beating a number of manufacturer teams, and I am looking forward to working with JEV and everyone in TECHEETAH to start this new chapter in my racing career". #FormulaE #Motorsport #ElectricStreetRacing
